    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** - May 5, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🧾 OpenAI let PwC turn finance into agent homework\n\nEnterprise AI has discovered the CFO office. The spreadsheets should have seen this coming.\n\n- **The build:** OpenAI and PwC announced a collaboration to build agents for planning, forecasting, reporting, procurement, payments, treasury, tax and accounting close.\n- **The lab:** OpenAI is the test case: its finance team says Codex helped process 5x more contracts with the same-sized team, while IR-GPT handled 200+ investor interactions during the recent fundraise.\n- **The packaging:** PwC will take the pattern to CFOs with controls, governance and human oversight attached.\n\n*Accounting software was not content being boring. It wanted agency.*\n\n**Sources:** [OpenAI](https://openai.com/index/openai-pwc-finance-collaboration/) | [PwC](https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/pwc-and-openai-build-a-first-of-its-kind-openai-native-finance-function-302762032.html)\n\n---\n\n## 🏗️ Anthropic and OpenAI found a new sales channel: private equity\n\nThe enterprise AI bottleneck is not model quality anymore. It is apparently finding enough adults to wire the thing into payroll.\n\n- **Anthropic:** It launched an AI services company with Blackstone, Hellman & Friedman and Goldman Sachs, backed by Apollo, General Atlantic, GIC, Leonard Green and Sequoia.\n- **OpenAI:** TechCrunch cites Bloomberg reporting that OpenAI is raising for The Development Company, targeting $4 billion from 19 investors at a $10 billion valuation.\n- **The trick:** Alternative asset managers get deployment teams inside their portfolio companies. AI labs get fewer beautiful demos and more invoices.\n\n*Consulting has been reinvented. Somehow, it looks exactly like consulting with GPUs.*\n\n**Sources:** [Anthropic](https://www.anthropic.com/news/enterprise-ai-services-company) | [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/04/anthropic-and-openai-are-both-launching-joint-ventures-for-enterprise-ai-services/)\n\n---\n\n## 💸 Sierra raised $950M because customer service agents are now infrastructure\n\nThe call-center replacement business has reached the very calm valuation phase.\n\n- **The round:** Bret Taylor and Clay Bavor's Sierra announced a $950 million raise led by Tiger Global and GV, pushing its post-money valuation above $15 billion.\n- **The traction:** Sierra says more than 40% of the Fortune 50 use its platform, with agents handling billions of interactions across mortgages, insurance claims, returns and fundraising.\n- **The signal:** The company said it hit $100 million ARR in November, then $150 million ARR in February.\n\n*The phone tree is not dead. It has simply raised growth capital and learned to say unfortunately with a model swarm.*\n\n**Sources:** [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/04/sierra-raises-950m-as-the-race-to-own-enterprise-ai-gets-serious/) | [Axios](https://www.axios.com/pro/enterprise-software-deals/2026/05/04/sierra-ai-valuation-agentic-enterprise)\n\n---\n\n## 🧱 IBM turned agentic AI into a governance appliance\n\nIBM heard the phrase agentic enterprise and immediately reached for a control plane. Honestly, fair.\n\n- **The stack:** At Think 2026, IBM announced watsonx Orchestrate private preview for multi-agent orchestration, IBM Concert public preview for operations and IBM Sovereign Core general availability.\n- **The data layer:** IBM is pairing Confluent integrations with watsonx.data and claims a Nestlé proof of concept delivered 83% cost savings and 30x price-performance improvement on a global data mart.\n- **The sovereignty bit:** Sovereign Core is built for customer-controlled identity, encryption, logs, audit evidence and governed AI execution.\n\n*The agent revolution has reached the paperwork phase. IBM has been training for this for decades.*\n\n**Sources:** [IBM Think](https://newsroom.ibm.com/2026-05-05-Think-2026-IBM-Delivers-the-Blueprint-for-the-AI-Operating-Model-as-the-AI-Divide-Widens) | [IBM Sovereign Core](https://newsroom.ibm.com/2026-05-05-Think-2026-IBM-Makes-Digital-Sovereignty-Operational-with-General-Availability-of-IBM-Sovereign-Core)\n"
  }
]
